The paper deals with developing algorithms for evaluating queries to Horn knowledge bases, which is a topic in database systems (cs.DB). The use of iterative deepening search and control strategies suggests an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) aspect to the work. The paper also discusses the efficiency of query processing, which could fall under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The use of set-at-a-time operations and tail recursion elimination suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes a generic evaluation method, which could be relevant to software engineering (cs.SE).
